.SH BUILTINS

The following builtin commands are supported:

.IT
.B env
- displays the environment variables

.B exit
- exits the program

.B setenv
- sets the environment variables

.B unsetenv
- removes elements from the environment

Example of a builtin command:
.IP
.br
.\&
.RS
\&$ env
.br
\&TERM=xterm-256color
.br
\&SHELL=/bin/bash
.br
\&SSH_CLIENT=10.0.2.2 50046 22
.br
\&OLDPWD=/home/vagrant
.br
\&SSH_TTY=/dev/pts/0
.br
\&LC_ALL=en_US
.br
\&USER=vagrant
.br
\&MAIL=/var/mail/vagrant
.br
\&PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin
.br
\&PWD=/home/vagrant/basic_shell
.br
\&LANG=en_US.UTF-8
.br
\&SHLVL=1
.br
\&HOME=/home/vagrant
.br
\&LOGNAME=vagrant
.br
\&SSH_CONNECTION=10.0.2.2 50046 10.0.2.15 22
.br
\&LESSOPEN=| /usr/bin/lesspipe %s
.br
\&LESSCLOSE=/usr/bin/lesspipe %s %s
.br
\&_=./hsh
.br
\&$


